                    "body": "Probably the easiest thing to do is when the failure occurs the file writer should take whatever rows it has reserved from the backpressure and release them.  The only tricky part is that the failure is going to pop up from an I/O thread and so we need to make sure we're properly guarding access to the backpressure to avoid race conditions.",
